sql:
SELECT users.user_name, performance.attempt_date, performance.feedback
FROM users
JOIN performance ON users.user_id = performance.user_id;

SELECT question_id, question_text, correct_answer, distractor_1, distractor_2, distractor_3, complexity_level, question_type, source
FROM questions
WHERE topic_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
1. 'moderately challenging' refers to questions with a complexity level of 2;
2. 'introductory subject' correlates to topic ID 1;
3. 'the guy named Bob Williams' specifies the author of the questions whose user name is 'Bob Williams'.

- "more attention this year" refers to the period from January 1, 2023, to June 30, 2023;
- "number of questions raised" indicates that the query is concerned with questions created within the specified period;
- "typical rating of the resources" refers to the average rating of resources associated with each topic.
